==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Water cock
<hw>Wa"ter cock`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A large
gallinule (<spn>Gallicrex cristatus</spn>) native of Australia, India,
and the East Indies. In the breeding season the male is black and has a
fleshy red caruncle, or horn, on the top of its head. Called also
<altname>kora</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Water color</ent>⟦br⟧
